    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                <ol cols="2" marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Work out: <m>\sqrt{0.81}</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>\sqrt{0.81}</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Since <m>0.81</m> can be written as the fraction <m>\frac{81}{100}</m>, we take the square root of both the numerator and the denominator separately. 
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                \sqrt{0.81} = \sqrt{\frac{81}{100}} = \frac{\sqrt{81}}{\sqrt{100}}
                            </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Here, we express <m>81</m> and <m>100</m> in terms of their prime factors to simplify the square root calculation.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                \frac{\sqrt{81}}{\sqrt{100}} = \frac{\sqrt{{\color{red}3} \times {\color{red}3} \times {\color{blue}3} \times {\color{blue}3}}}{\sqrt{{\color{red}2} \times {\color{red}2} \times {\color{blue}5} \times {\color{blue}5}}}
                            </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Select one factor from each pair and multiply the selected factors.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                \frac{{\color{red}3} \times {\color{blue}3} }{{\color{red}2} \times {\color{blue}5}} = \frac{9}{10}
                            </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Divide the results:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                \frac{9}{10} = 0.9
                            </me>
                            
                            <me>
                                = 0.9
                            </me>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
